<title>USA: Valley Systems settles litigation.</title>
<headline>Valley Systems settles litigation.</headline>
<dateline>CANAL FULTON, Ohio 1996-12-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Valley Systems Inc on Monday said it settled all litigation that the company had brought in 1993 against former officers and directors.  </p>
<p>The company said the settlement will result in an increase to net income of about $750,000 in its second quarter ending December 31.</p>
<p>It also said its majority shareholder, Rollins Investment Fund, had extended its existing $9 million line of credit for an additional two years, to July 2000.</p>
<p>Valley Systems provides specialized cleaning and other services to industry and businesses through the use of ultra high pressure water jet technology, as well as water blasting, vacuum, and other procedures.</p>
<p>-- New York Newsdesk 212 859-1610</p>
